<h1>Introduction to EMV for Public Transport</h1>

<p>EMV (Europay, Mastercard, and Visa) is the global standard for secure, contactless payments using smart cards and mobile devices. In the context of mass transit, EMV brings convenience and interoperability, allowing passengers to pay directly with their bank-issued cards or digital wallets.</p>

<h2>What You'll Learn</h2>
<ul>
  <li>The fundamentals of EMV and how contactless technology works</li>
  <li>Benefits of open-loop payments for transit authorities and users</li>
  <li>Comparison between EMV and traditional closed-loop fare media</li>
  <li>Challenges in implementation and key success cases globally</li>
</ul>

<p>This module is ideal for public sector decision-makers, finance professionals, and transportation planners seeking to understand the foundations of EMV acceptance in transit systems.</p>
